         <p class="- topic/p ">A manual bypass
switch is used to isolate sections for maintenance while supplying
the load from the bypass mains.<ph otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/ph "> A 2-position
manual bypass switch have the positions <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>.</ph>
            <ph otherprops="tempInclude 3pMBS" class="- topic/ph "> A 3-position manual bypass
switch have the positions <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b>, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>.</ph>
         </p>
         <p otherprops="tempExclude" class="- topic/p ">There are two different manual
bypass switches:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">2-position, with the positions <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">3-postion, with the positions <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b>, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </div>
      <p class="- topic/p ">When the manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> position the system
can automatically switch between normal operation and bypass operation
without interruption.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p "> The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position is used to isolate sections for maintenances
or troubleshooting.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position is used to test the function of the static
switch EN or troubleshoot the system.<ph otherprops="tempExclude 2pMBS" class="- topic/ph "> In a 2-position manual bypass switch the test position is equivalent
with closing the EN input switch in the position <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>.</ph>
      </p>
